Consent:
AGREEMENT TO PARTICIPATE

 

STUDY LEADERSHIP.   We are asking you to take part in a research project that is led by Gabriel Cook and Daniel Krauss, professors of psychology at Claremont McKenna College (CMC). gcook@CMC.edu

 

PURPOSE.  The purpose of this study is to understand how jurors make decisions about civil hearings involving sexual violence.

 

PARTICIPATION.  During the research study, you will be asked to read various materials and render decisions concerning what you think should occur if you were a juror in the case. 

 

RISKS OF PARTICIPATION.  There are minimal potential physical, psychological, social, or legal risks involved in participating in this study. The procedures of this study are consistent with sound research in the field. You will be exposed to the stress and anxiety of determining whether an individual should be civilly committed. At any time, however, participants will be free to discontinue their participation if they feel disquieted by the proceedings.  There are no other foreseeable risks. 

 

BENEFITS OF PARTICIPATION.  We expect the study to have potential personal benefits. The potential benefits include an opportunity to participate in a study with important practical implications about civil hearings, to learn about the interaction between psychology and law, and to learn about current methods of scientific studies.

 

VOLUNTARY PARTICIPATION.  Your participation in this study is completely voluntary.  You may stop or withdraw from the study at any time or refuse to answer any particular question for any reason without it being held against you.  Your decision whether or not to participate will have no external effects other than your compensation for your participation.

 

CONFIDENTIALITY.  Your individual privacy will be protected in all papers, books, talks, posts, or stories resulting from this study.  We may share the data we collect with other researchers, but we will not reveal your identity with it. In order to ensure confidentiality of your responses, you will be assigned an ID number. This ID number will be used on your data sheets and demographic survey results. We will not connect your name to the data and no other identifying information will appear on the data sheets. There will be no way for the researcher to identify participants or their responses. All data will be stored on password protected programs and servers.

 

CONSENT. By proceeding, you agree to participate voluntarily.
